2 | P a g e

Experiment Number: 02

Experiment Name: A seven-segment display starts with the last digit of your roll number

and continue counting the rest of all digits.

Working Procedure: In this lab task the condition is, the last digit of my roll number is

display fast then continue the rest of all digit display in seven-segment display using arduino.

My roll number is 11, according to the condition last digit of my roll number is 1, so seven- segment display first display 1 then display rest of all digit. In this lab task, for better

understanding and ease of work, I am dividing it into 13 steps.

Step-1:

In the first step I design the connection of arduiono to seven-segment display. In the proteus,

the pick devices first I took ARDUINO UNO and then took Seven-Segment-Com-Cathode.Then

Arduiono’s pin 1 connect seven-segment’s pin 1,like this connect all pin order to 2,3,4,5,6,7

serially .And last pin of seven-segment display’s connect Ground.

Fig-1.1: Connection of Arduino to seven-segment display in proteus.

Step-2:

In the second step, I code the problem using Arduino software. At first in setup function I

declare how many pin number use in this problem and output of the pinnumber.
